President Trump participated in the Arab Islamic American Summit in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. He thanked King Salman and the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia for hosting the summit and expressed gratitude to the foreign leaders in attendance. The President emphasized the historic nature of the summit and highlighted the agreements made with Saudi Arabia, which will lead to significant investments and job creation. President Trump also outlined his administration's approach to international relations, emphasizing support for friends and determination against enemies. He addressed the threat of terrorism and expressed the United States' commitment to standing with its allies in combating this evil. The President urged the nations of the Middle East to take responsibility for shaping their own future and that of their countries and children.